    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Oil Cooler and Filter Housing - Removal</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26509.2">
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Oil Filter Housing</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, make sure that the engine has cooled down
                        sufficiently before attempting to remove any components. See
                        <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e3001003" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj11/J11023.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the oil filter cap</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen oil filter cap and allow oil to drain through filter housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001004" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj11/J11024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the oil filter and cap assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil filter and cap as a unit and discard O-ring gasket on cap.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not attempt to remove latching return tube unless oil filter
                        housing and oil filter base have been separated.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the one bolt (M8 x 50) securing the oil filter housing to the oil filter
                    adapter.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two stud bolts (M8 x 50 x 16) securing the oil filter housing to the intake
                    manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the six screws (M6 x 25) securing the oil filter housing to the oil filter base.
                    Remove and discard oil filter assembly gasket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001005" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ13/J13039.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Latching return tube assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Latching return tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Viton O-ring seal, size #122</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter housing</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="e3001006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ13/J13037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the latching return tube assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil filter latching return tube by pushing down and rotating tube
                    counter-clockwise 120&#176;, then lift tube straight up. Remove O-ring seal and discard.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
